[Student "S"]
{EAST might jump-shift, but with no 5-card suit prefers to use Jacoby 2NT.

WEST shows some extra strength plus a 5-card \C suit with his 4\C bid. 

When EAST's Blackwood discovers two Aces in WEST's hand she goes right to 7\S. 
She knows WEST has only three red cards and her \HA 
\D A K will take care of them. She figures WEST can ruff 
out any \C losers.}

